results.lead_paragraph: VIENNA, June 16 President Carter and Leonid I. Brezhnev, the Soviet leader, expressed mutual desire at the opening of their summit conference here today to continue efforts to control nuclear arms. headline.main: One of the Few Who Got the Job--Astronaut

results.snippet: CAPE CANAVERAL, Fla.--To most of the high-ranking women in the space industry here, the most coveted job is that of astronaut. In fact, several women who work as engineers said they applied for astronaut training in 1977, but were rejected.
